cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents an algorithm for computing all $q$-gram frequencies on a compressed string represented as a collage system. This involves designing an efficient data structure and algorithm for the problem, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms.
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper analyzes the time and space complexity of the proposed algorithm, which is a key aspect of computational complexity theory.
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with text compression algorithms and their representation using collage systems, which is related to information theory.
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed algorithm can potentially be parallelized to improve its performance, which falls under the scope of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing.
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper presents an algorithm for a practical problem of computing $q$-gram frequencies on compressed strings, which can have applications in computational engineering, finance, and science.
